.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-STATUS-RESOURCE-GET 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.9.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-status\-resource\-get \- Fetch one supported live Grafana resource by selector.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util status resource get [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Fetch one supported live Grafana resource by selector.
.PP
Use this when you need the live payload for one supported resource item and want a simpler generic query than building a full export or inspect workflow.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B positional SELECTOR
required <kind>/<identity> selector, for example dashboards/cpu\-main or datasources/prom\-main
.TP
.B \-\-profile, \-\-url, \-\-token, \-\-basic\-user, \-\-basic\-password
live Grafana connection settings
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format
choose text, table, json, or yaml
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Fetch one supported live Grafana resource by selector.
.EX
grafana-util status resource get dashboards/cpu-main --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1)
